<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Pearson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-02-07"><hi rend="italic">February 7,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay advises Mr. Pearson that Consul Norton’s special functions
                            ceased when the Department telegraphed to the legation on January 11
                            that he might return to his post. Instructs him that full compliance
                            with the terms of the settlement must be insisted upon.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>